# Web Structure

## Page files

- `app/**/page.tsx` stays thin — layout and composition only
- If `page.tsx` exceeds ~120 lines, split into `components/` or a feature folder

## Components

- Extract when reused **or** inline JSX exceeds ~40 lines
- Move colocated helpers (e.g. `ThemeImage` in `page.tsx`) to `components/` when they grow or are reused

## Styles

- Tailwind CSS v4 utilities in markup; entrypoint is `app/globals.css`
- Shared tokens in `:root` / `@theme`; page-specific values use arbitrary utilities first
- Extract `@utility` or `@layer components` only for stable, repeated primitives

## Boundaries

- Server Components by default
- Add `'use client'` only when hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers require it

## Adding features

1. Page in `app/**/page.tsx` (thin)
2. Reusable UI in `components/` or feature-scoped folder
3. Shared logic in `lib/` or `hooks/` when used across routes
